                <h1>Navajo Tribe: Cultural Heritage and Community</h1>
                <p>The Navajo Tribe, known as the Diné, is a Native American nation located in the Southwestern United States. Renowned for their rich culture, intricate weaving, and beautiful jewelry, they also have a deep connection to their land and traditions. Their language, ceremonies, and artistry reflect a profound spiritual heritage, uniting their community.</p>
